title: Cottrell to Hendricks
commentTextItems: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length at the body, turned down to long leg'}]
commentPreTextItems:
[{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'The teams are on their way out, it should be a decent affair this and West Indies might actually have a chance of winning for once! Sheldon Cottrell to open the bowling...'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '5.50pm We got there in the end. No Marchant de Lange for the host which is perhaps surprising - maybe because they have selected two allrounders in Parnell and Wiese.'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Almost time for the toss, the captains are coming out in very hot conditions - beautiful day in Cape Town. Pitch looks solid but perhaps a little grass, one across from the Test wicket. South Africa have won the toss and will bat, interesting to see the teams...'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'South Africa 1 Morne van Wyk, 2 Reeza Hendricks, 3 Rilee Roussow, 4 Faf du Plessis (capt), 5 David Miller, 6 Farhaan Behardien, 7 David Wiese, 8 Wayne Parnell, 9 Kyle Abbott, 10 Kagiso Rabada, 11 Imran Tahir'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "Just waiting for the West Indies XI. The one we've been given has Dwayne Bravo in it, the same Bravo who is supposedly currently in Australia. All sorts of confusion but it does appear the Bravo has boarded a plane and is set to play here..."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'West Indies 1 Chris Gayle, 2 Dwyane Smith, 3 Marlon Samuels, 4 Dwayne Bravo, 5 Kieron Pollard, 6 Denesh D Ramdin, 7 Darren Sammy, 8 Andre Russell, 9 Jason Holder, 10 Ashley Nurse, 11 Sheldon Cottrell'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "5.15pm Afternoon folks and welcome to the first T20 from Cape Town. In the context of the cricket to come this is an odd series that doesn't really fit, but it represents West Indies' best chance of success on this tour. They have a strong looking squad while South Africa have rested a few players, although still have plenty of talent. Toss and teams coming in just over ten minutes."}]

title: Russell to du Plessis
commentTextItems: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full length just outside off, driven well down the ground, straight to mid-off but through his fingers! The fielder was well in from the rope, had he been back it was an easy take, still got there with a leap but couldn't cling on"}]

title: Russell to du Plessis
commentTextItems: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length on the stumps, pulled powerfully away and finds the gap wide of midwicket'}]

title: Russell to du Plessis
commentTextItems: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full toss on the stumps, tried to be flicked leg side but gets a big leading edge that's taken by mid-on! A real bonus wicket, poor ball really but du Plessis totally miscued it and it presented a simple chance for Sammy"}]

commentPostTextItems:
[{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'So the Gayle-force blows in to Cape Town. Will he travel up to the Wanderers on Sunday? 1pm start. Join us then...'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "Presentation time. I wonder who might be Man of the Match? Oh yes, it's Chris Gayle, the fastest fifty for the West Indies. 11 balls for 52 runs in the middle of his innings, incredible stuff today."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Here\'s Faf du Plessis: "It\'s a captain\'s nightmare. Tough for the bowler but a real learning curve for them. He\'s done that to every attack in the world. If you don\'t get him out he\'s going to hurt you. We had a small opportunity with a catch just out of Rilee\'s reach and you have to take those. I thought we posted a really good total, average at Newlands is about 150. We brought it back well at the end but we were just on the end of Chris Gayle today."'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "West Indies got on top with the ball quite quickly with regular wickets and it took Rilee Rossouw to ensure the hosts had a solid total to bowl at but nothing was big enough for Gayle in today's mood. He bludgeoned the ball to all parts and having flown in a few days ago, he's blasted his side to a first win on this tour. Amazing how the short format brings out the best in the West Indies. They're one-up in this three-match series."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'And Darren Sammy: "We were determined to make up for the Test series. This is a format we\'re very confident with. The beauty of our team is the power hitters. It was hard to pick the XI. But we\'re going to play free and fearless, sometime it may look sloppy but that\'s the way we\'re going to play. Chris gives himself a chance, sees what the wicket does and then it\'s helter-skelter. But also, Jason Holder bowled well up front but we didn\'t start or finish out overs well enough - the first and last balls we conceded too many boundaries."'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "The chase fizzed out remarkably and West Indies have won by four wickets but in reality this has been a hammering. Chris Gayle produced a real special, we don't often get it nowadays on the international stage but today he was brilliant and destroyed the South Africans. When he got out, West Indies slightly laboured but still got home with plenty in hand, even if they did take almost all the time available to them."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}]
